note:
4.2 ~ 92% ($19.75)
Mildiani 🇬🇪 Kindzmarauli 2019
Medium bodied, but full taste ~ red fruity cherries, dark berries, vanilla, and oak, semi sweet (42 gs/12% abv).
Just a deelish wine; right in my wheelhouse ~ sort of a port lite, with abt half the sugar and abv ~ using the Saperavi grape 🍇 from the Kakheti region of Georgia ~ the cradle of wine with 8,000 😳 years of wine tradition. 
I paired it up with some mid day grape rolls and baclava 😚. Fairly priced here, but, if it dropped on sale, I’d buy half a case.
